00:28:40,181 --> 00:28:43,182
Please, you've got to believe me.

258
00:29:10,336 --> 00:29:13,421
(SOFT, EERIE SNARLING)

259
00:29:24,350 --> 00:29:25,892
(SOFT, EERIE HOWL)

260
00:29:40,241 --> 00:29:42,530
(WEAKLY) Please, wait, please...

261
00:29:45,288 --> 00:29:47,123
Wait, please...

262
00:29:47,123 --> 00:29:49,167
Please don't do this to me.

263
00:29:49,167 --> 00:29:50,958
Relax. It won't hurt you.

264
00:29:52,545 --> 00:29:56,257
(GASPS) Call Dr Stringer, please.

265
00:29:56,257 --> 00:29:58,593
I'm right here, I'm right here.

266
00:29:58,593 --> 00:30:01,012
Please... Please...

267
00:30:01,012 --> 00:30:04,933
This is a bit. Bite down on it
or you'll bite your tongue off.

268
00:30:04,933 --> 00:30:09,020
No, please... (MUFFLED PLEADING)

269
00:30:09,020 --> 00:30:11,731
The medications
aren't working as I'd hope.

270
00:30:11,731 --> 00:30:14,981
This treatment should be beneficial.
(MUFFLED PLEADING)

271
00:30:19,405 --> 00:30:22,490
(ELECTRICITY ZAPS)
(WHIMPERS)

272
00:30:38,424 --> 00:30:41,177
I thought they stopped
using electroshock.

273
00:30:41,177 --> 00:30:42,720
Just look at her.

274
00:30:42,720 --> 00:30:46,057
She was all riled-up before,
now she's docile as a lamb.

275
00:30:46,057 --> 00:30:49,310
Hell, I wish they'd do it
to all the patients here,

276
00:30:49,310 --> 00:30:51,801
just fry the crazy
right out of them.

277
00:30:53,189 --> 00:30:55,941
(LOCK CLANKS)

278
00:30:58,278 --> 00:31:01,362
(BIRD SQUAWKS)

279
00:31:09,622 --> 00:31:11,531
Come on, sleepyhead.

280
00:31:12,875 --> 00:31:15,449
It's time to wake up. Come on.

281
00:31:16,713 --> 00:31:18,207
Come on.

282
00:31:22,218 --> 00:31:25,302
(CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYS SOFTLY)

283
00:32:07,555 --> 00:32:12,632
So, since we have a new member,
let's go over the rules.

284
00:32:13,770 --> 00:32:16,147
Everyone gets a chance to talk.

285
00:32:16,147 --> 00:32:18,021
No interrupting.

286
00:32:19,359 --> 00:32:21,110
Just say what's on your minds.

287
00:32:21,110 --> 00:32:23,269
Who'd like to begin?

288
00:32:28,868 --> 00:32:30,362
Emily?

289
00:32:33,206 --> 00:32:34,999
What did you do to Kristen?

290
00:32:34,999 --> 00:32:38,795
We had to have a little unscheduled
therapy last night.

291
00:32:38,795 --> 00:32:40,421
Is that what you call it?

292
00:32:40,421 --> 00:32:42,632
It's nothing to be
alarmed about, Emily.

293
00:32:42,632 --> 00:32:46,131
Sometimes when you take people away,
they don't come back.

294
00:32:47,512 --> 00:32:49,681
Tammy didn't come back.

295
00:32:49,681 --> 00:32:51,641
Who's Tammy?

296
00:32:51,641 --> 00:32:53,893
She's the last one that got out.

297
00:32:53,893 --> 00:32:55,353
What did you say?

298
00:32:55,353 --> 00:32:59,023
Iris, you know we don't discuss
people who aren't present.

299
00:32:59,023 --> 00:33:01,317
Wait. Why can't we talk
about Tammy?

300
00:33:01,317 --> 00:33:03,278
Who's Tammy?

301
00:33:03,278 --> 00:33:05,769
Zoey, how do you feel
about all this?

302
00:33:09,158 --> 00:33:10,569
(WHISPERS) Zoey?

303
00:33:16,291 --> 00:33:17,834
OK.

304
00:33:17,834 --> 00:33:22,377
Let's discuss what happened yesterday,
shall we, in the showers?

305
00:33:23,881 --> 00:33:25,341
Kristen?

306
00:33:25,341 --> 00:33:30,138
Well... I didn't see a thing.

307
00:33:30,138 --> 00:33:31,848
I believe her.

308
00:33:31,848 --> 00:33:35,977
(CHUCKLES) Great. That's someone
you want on your side.

309
00:33:35,977 --> 00:33:39,061
(BIRD SQUAWKS)

310
00:33:41,232 --> 00:33:42,940
Are you OK?

311
00:33:46,696 --> 00:33:49,198
I don't know what's going on
in this place.

312
00:33:49,198 --> 00:33:51,274
It'll be OK.

313
00:33:52,452 --> 00:33:56,122
I can tell you are strong.
(HUMMING)

314
00:33:56,122 --> 00:33:58,708
See you later, alligators.

315
00:33:58,708 --> 00:34:02,503
I'm off to what should be
my last session with Stringer.

316
00:34:02,503 --> 00:34:05,715
What do you mean?
I mean, I'm being released.

317
00:34:05,715 --> 00:34:08,134
That's impossible.
I've been here longer than you.

318
00:34:08,134 --> 00:34:11,137
Stringer told you
he was releasing you?

319
00:34:11,137 --> 00:34:16,142
Not in those words, but he said
I'm making great progress.

320
00:34:16,142 --> 00:34:19,938
You're not going anywhere.
Yes, I am.

321
00:34:19,938 --> 00:34:22,065
How did you get him
to release you, though?

322
00:34:22,065 --> 00:34:24,192
How did you act? What did you say?

323
00:34:24,192 --> 00:34:27,862
I didn't act cured, Kristen,
if that's what you're getting at.

324
00:34:27,862 --> 00:34:29,653
I am cured.

325
00:34:32,283 --> 00:34:33,777
I'm ready.

326
00:34:38,498 --> 00:34:40,750
Do you really think
she's getting outta here?

327
00:34:40,750 --> 00:34:43,455
(DOOR CLOSES)
(LAUGHS)

328
00:34:45,129 --> 00:34:47,834
How have you been feeling?
Better.

329
00:34:48,967 --> 00:34:50,843
I've been drawing a lot.

330
00:34:50,843 --> 00:34:53,595
And I'm getting along with everybody,
even the new girl.

331
00:34:54,931 --> 00:34:57,303
I have some of
your latest work here.

332
00:34:59,477 --> 00:35:01,137
Where did you get those?

333
00:35:03,606 --> 00:35:06,734
You really managed
to capture her essence.

334
00:35:06,734 --> 00:35:08,486
I was just fooling around.

335
00:35:08,486 --> 00:35:11,572
You're really quite talented, Iris.

336
00:35:11,572 --> 00:35:13,364
I'm practically cured,
don't you think?

337
00:35:16,286 --> 00:35:18,329
That's an old one.

338
00:35:18,329 --> 00:35:20,957
I'm not like that anymore, really.

339
00:35:20,957 --> 00:35:23,626
You're making considerable progress.

340
00:35:23,626 --> 00:35:25,128
So I can go?

341
00:35:25,128 --> 00:35:27,001
Let's see how things go today, hmm?

342
00:35:29,716 --> 00:35:32,503
The others didn't believe me.
They don't think that I'm better.

343
00:35:35,054 --> 00:35:36,764
Why are you doing that?

344
00:35:36,764 --> 00:35:39,552
I'd like to try something
a little different this time.

345
00:35:45,189 --> 00:35:48,526
What is that?
It's a metronome.

346
00:35:48,526 --> 00:35:51,064
(STEADY CLICKING)

347
00:35:55,408 --> 00:35:57,452
Listen to the rhythm.

348
00:35:57,452 --> 00:35:59,694
It'll help you to relax.

349
00:36:02,081 --> 00:36:04,157
OK, close your eyes.

350
00:36:08,963 --> 00:36:12,083
I haven't had any problems
in a while.

351
00:36:14,177 --> 00:36:17,555
I'm feeling better. Healthier.

352
00:36:17,555 --> 00:36:20,093
Focus on your home.

353
00:36:21,184 --> 00:36:22,435
Imagine it.

354
00:36:22,435 --> 00:36:25,730
Imagine your parents there
waiting for you.

355
00:36:25,730 --> 00:36:28,483
(BREATHES RAGGEDLY)

356
00:36:28,483 --> 00:36:31,319
I'm starting to get sleepy.

357
00:36:31,319 --> 00:36:33,892
Can you describe your home for me?

358
00:36:36,240 --> 00:36:38,399
What colour is your house?

359
00:36:41,829 --> 00:36:45,697
We live... in a little white house.

360
00:36:48,419 --> 00:36:51,673
I have to... go to sleep.

361
00:36:51,673 --> 00:36:57,178
It's September 3, 1958.

362
00:36:57,178 --> 00:36:59,055
It's night-time.

363
00:36:59,055 --> 00:37:02,056
You are asleep in your bedroom.

364
00:37:03,810 --> 00:37:06,894
(CLICKING FADES)

365
00:37:09,983 --> 00:37:12,022
She's asleep in my office.

366
00:37:18,658 --> 00:37:20,152
Where did she go?

367
00:37:26,874 --> 00:37:28,369
Find her.

368
00:37:29,877 --> 00:37:33,006
(SHUFFLING FOOTSTEPS ECHO,
WHEELS RATTLE)

369
00:37:33,006 --> 00:37:35,300
(EERIE BREATHING)
Where are we going?

370
00:37:35,300 --> 00:37:38,177
(DISTANT SCREAMING)

371
00:37:38,177 --> 00:37:39,672
No.

372
00:37:42,974 --> 00:37:44,682
This isn't right.

373
00:37:46,436 --> 00:37:48,843
(PANTS) No.

374
00:37:50,732 --> 00:37:54,569
(DISTANT SHRIEKING)
No! NO! NO! NO!

375
00:37:54,569 --> 00:37:56,738
NO! NO!

376
00:37:56,738 --> 00:37:58,615
NO! NO!

377
00:37:58,615 --> 00:38:01,993
(WHIMPERS) Oh, please don't.
Please don't hurt me, please.

378
00:38:01,993 --> 00:38:04,454
I'm so sorry.

379
00:38:04,454 --> 00:38:07,624
I'm so sorry. I'm so sorry.

380
00:38:07,624 --> 00:38:11,289
I just wanna go home.
I just wanna go home.

381
00:38:14,213 --> 00:38:16,841
NO! Oh, my God, No! Please!

382
00:38:16,841 --> 00:38:19,552
Please don't do this!
Please! Please!

383
00:38:19,552 --> 00:38:22,305
(WHIMPERS) No. Help!

384
00:38:22,305 --> 00:38:25,389
(SCREAMS)

385
00:38:26,684 --> 00:38:28,677
NO! NO!

386
00:38:31,522 --> 00:38:33,681
(SQUELCHING)

387
00:38:36,402 --> 00:38:38,196
(FOOTSTEPS FADE)

388
00:38:38,196 --> 00:38:41,280
(CHEERY MUSIC PLAYS ON TV)

389
00:39:02,595 --> 00:39:04,387
It's alright.

390
00:39:05,765 --> 00:39:08,518
(SQUEAKS) Where's Iris?

391
00:39:08,518 --> 00:39:11,269
She's not back yet?

392
00:39:13,189 --> 00:39:15,566
OK, time for bed.

393
00:39:15,566 --> 00:39:17,527
Where's Iris?

394
00:39:17,527 --> 00:39:19,934
Come on, time for bed.

395
00:39:38,089 --> 00:39:40,662
Go to sleep.

396
00:39:50,602 --> 00:39:53,686
(EERIE WHISPERING)

397
00:40:04,198 --> 00:40:07,283
(DOOR THUDS)

398
00:40:14,917 --> 00:40:18,084
(THUNDER CRACKS)
(FAINT WHIMPERING)

399
00:40:22,717 --> 00:40:25,637
(CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYS SOFTLY)

400
00:40:25,637 --> 00:40:27,722
Anyone see Iris today?

401
00:40:27,722 --> 00:40:31,554
Maybe they let her go home.
No way.

402
00:40:52,497 --> 00:40:54,082
Nurse Lundt.

403
00:40:54,082 --> 00:40:56,489
Please, Nurse Lundt.

404
00:40:58,044 --> 00:40:59,622
Where's Iris?

405
00:41:02,590 --> 00:41:05,508
If she went home, why didn't
she take her sketchbook?

406
00:41:08,137 --> 00:41:11,641
You can't get them to tell you anything
around here.

407
00:41:11,641 --> 00:41:13,598
Trust me, I've tried.

408
00:41:55,852 --> 00:41:58,936
(EERIE WHISPERING)

409
00:42:21,294 --> 00:42:23,583
Kristen, tell me
what's bothering you.

410
00:42:29,469 --> 00:42:32,090
Did you treat a girl named Alice?

411
00:42:33,306 --> 00:42:34,884
Where did you hear that name?

412
00:42:36,184 --> 00:42:38,853
That's who attacked me
in the showers.

413
00:42:38,853 --> 00:42:41,807
You're not gonna answer me, are you?

414
00:42:42,899 --> 00:42:44,651
What happened to Iris?

415
00:42:44,651 --> 00:42:48,237
How many girls have disappeared
at this hospital?

416
00:42:48,237 --> 00:42:51,366
Nurse Lundt was wiping someone's
name off the door when I got here.

417
00:42:51,366 --> 00:42:53,409
Well, you were heavily sedated.

418
00:42:53,409 --> 00:42:55,449
I'm sure you believe
you saw what you say.

419
00:42:57,997 --> 00:43:00,156
It happened.

420
00:43:06,047 --> 00:43:07,590
What happened to them?

421
00:43:07,590 --> 00:43:09,217
To whom?

422
00:43:09,217 --> 00:43:12,301
To Iris, Alice, Tammy.

423
00:43:14,305 --> 00:43:15,930
Are they dead?

424
00:43:17,141 --> 00:43:19,217
Why would you think they're dead?

425
00:43:22,563 --> 00:43:24,640
There's a ghost in here.

426
00:43:26,818 --> 00:43:28,478
A ghost?

427
00:43:30,571 --> 00:43:33,825
What does it look like?
A girl.

428
00:43:33,825 --> 00:43:36,995
The girl that attacked me
in the shower.

429
00:43:36,995 --> 00:43:39,865
The one I see in the halls.

430
00:43:41,541 --> 00:43:44,711
Same with the other girls.
I know they've seen her too.

431
00:43:44,711 --> 00:43:50,583
So, please, tell me
what's going on here.

432
00:43:56,347 --> 00:43:57,599
Please.

433
00:43:57,599 --> 00:43:59,976
I can't give you the answers, Kristen.

434
00:43:59,976 --> 00:44:02,681
You have to find them for yourself.

435
00:44:03,771 --> 00:44:05,898
Goddammit! Tell me!

436
00:44:05,898 --> 00:44:08,443
Take Kristen back to her room.

437
00:44:08,443 --> 00:44:10,898
You just don't give up, do you?

438
00:44:17,201 --> 00:44:19,277
Let go of me!

439
00:44:28,421 --> 00:44:29,915
Who's Alice?

440
00:44:31,633 --> 00:44:34,918
You all know she's here,
so why won't you answer me?

441
00:44:36,220 --> 00:44:37,555
Look at me!

442
00:44:37,555 --> 00:44:40,509
Sorry, I don't converse
with loonies.

443
00:44:47,065 --> 00:44:48,858
Don't you ever call me that!

444
00:44:48,858 --> 00:44:51,402
Don't do this.
Tell me who Alice is.

445
00:44:51,402 --> 00:44:56,859
Alice Hudson was here. She was
one of us but she's gone now.

446
00:45:01,454 --> 00:45:02,948
Gone?

447
00:45:04,749 --> 00:45:07,999
Where?
She got out, they let her out.

448
00:45:13,216 --> 00:45:14,840
I'm getting outta here.

449
00:45:15,969 --> 00:45:17,136
Tonight.

450
00:45:17,136 --> 00:45:19,055
I'm gonna find Iris.

451
00:45:19,055 --> 00:45:20,598
Really?
Really.

452
00:45:20,598 --> 00:45:23,516
You can't get out.
Watch me.

453
00:45:25,144 --> 00:45:27,766
You coming with me?
(WHISPERS) How?

454
00:45:31,150 --> 00:45:32,977
Zoey, give me your penny.

455
00:45:45,456 --> 00:45:47,994
She won't let us leave.

456
00:45:52,547 --> 00:45:54,882
(PHONE RINGS)

457
00:45:54,882 --> 00:45:55,925
Hello?

458
00:45:55,925 --> 00:45:59,512
Leonard! Yes,
thanks for calling me back.

459
00:45:59,512 --> 00:46:02,181
I need a consult.

460
00:46:02,181 --> 00:46:05,182
Still the same lost causes, yes.

461
00:46:06,269 --> 00:46:09,647
The problem is that
things have begun to escalate.

462
00:46:09,647 --> 00:46:11,899
Alright. Let's see.

463
00:46:11,899 --> 00:46:14,402
I need you to shove this in here like this

464
00:46:14,402 --> 00:46:17,280
so it seems locked but you can
still open it from the outside.

465
00:46:17,280 --> 00:46:18,323
OK.

466
00:46:18,323 --> 00:46:19,866
And then you're gonna get into bed.

467
00:46:19,866 --> 00:46:22,736
Make sure you have all your clothes on,
but hide it with the covers.

468
00:46:24,912 --> 00:46:27,248
And then I'm gonna come
and get you after bed check.

469
00:46:27,248 --> 00:46:29,959
Then what?
Then we get Iris and get outta here.

470
00:46:29,959 --> 00:46:33,245
Why do you care so much about Iris?

471
00:46:35,089 --> 00:46:37,415
I care about getting us all
out of here alive.

472
00:46:48,353 --> 00:46:49,348
Open.

473
00:47:21,094 --> 00:47:24,095
Alright, we gotta go now. Come on.

474
00:47:47,620 --> 00:47:49,114
(DOOR TAPS SOFTLY)

475
00:48:15,773 --> 00:48:17,565
(SIGHS)

476
00:48:21,779 --> 00:48:23,274
(GRUNTS)

477
00:49:03,237 --> 00:49:04,233
(GASPS)

478
00:50:13,182 --> 00:50:14,677
(DOOR OPENS)

479
00:51:05,860 --> 00:51:08,102
I don't think this is the right way.

480
00:51:10,782 --> 00:51:12,276
Ah, in here.

481
00:51:20,124 --> 00:51:21,619
It's a morgue.

482
00:51:38,434 --> 00:51:39,845
(DOOR OPENS NEARBY)

483
00:51:42,772 --> 00:51:43,935
Hide!

484
00:51:54,659 --> 00:51:56,402
(PANTS)

485
00:52:04,502 --> 00:52:06,087
(DOOR CLOSES NEARBY)

486
00:52:06,087 --> 00:52:07,630
MAN: Someone's been in there.

487
00:52:07,630 --> 00:52:10,252
MAN 2: Come on,
let's take a look around.

488
00:52:16,014 --> 00:52:17,932
Do you see anything?

489
00:52:17,932 --> 00:52:18,928
No.

490
00:52:23,980 --> 00:52:26,553
(MEN'S VOICES RECEDE)

491
00:52:30,820 --> 00:52:32,314
(SIGHS)

492
00:52:47,545 --> 00:52:49,039
Emily?

493
00:52:53,468 --> 00:52:55,425
(RATTLING)

494
00:53:11,361 --> 00:53:12,904
Emily?

495
00:53:12,904 --> 00:53:14,980
Is that you?

496
00:54:10,044 --> 00:54:11,538
GIRL: Alice?

497
00:54:39,365 --> 00:54:40,859
Nice try.

498
00:55:31,542 --> 00:55:33,452
(GROANS)

499
00:55:51,980 --> 00:55:53,523
(WHISPERS) Kristen!

500
00:55:53,523 --> 00:55:57,026
Emily! What happened?

501
00:55:57,026 --> 00:55:59,696
Those orderlies caught me.

502
00:55:59,696 --> 00:56:02,490
And they hurt my arms.

503
00:56:02,490 --> 00:56:04,784
(SIGHS)

504
00:56:04,784 --> 00:56:06,661
Did you find Iris?

505
00:56:06,661 --> 00:56:08,371
No.

506
00:56:08,371 --> 00:56:09,956
No.

507
00:56:09,956 --> 00:56:12,281
She's gone.

508
00:56:13,501 --> 00:56:15,410
She's not coming back.

509
00:56:17,505 --> 00:56:20,842
Look, if we don't get out of here,

510
00:56:20,842 --> 00:56:22,385
we're next.

511
00:56:22,385 --> 00:56:24,710
We're not getting out.

512
00:56:25,888 --> 00:56:27,548
We have to try again.

513
00:56:28,641 --> 00:56:32,509
Nobody... gets out.

514
00:56:36,316 --> 00:56:37,691
Hello!

515
00:56:42,363 --> 00:56:45,700
So... Roy...
Not interested.

516
00:56:45,700 --> 00:56:47,744
You didn't even hear me out.

517
00:56:47,744 --> 00:56:49,787
Fine. Shoot.

518
00:56:49,787 --> 00:56:54,626
Well, I know you said you wouldn't
date any of us inside the ward.

519
00:56:54,626 --> 00:56:58,254
But I just know I'm getting out soon

520
00:56:58,254 --> 00:57:01,215
and I thought maybe you could
call me some time.

521
00:57:01,215 --> 00:57:06,763
There is no way I will
ever, ever date you.

522
00:57:06,763 --> 00:57:08,765
Got it?

523
00:57:08,765 --> 00:57:11,392
But I...
No! Not ever.

524
00:57:11,392 --> 00:57:15,604
Now, leave me alone. I'm swamped
here and I don't have time for this.

525
00:57:23,029 --> 00:57:26,612
(TV PLAYS SOFTLY)

526
00:57:28,451 --> 00:57:33,081
WOMAN ON TV: Tom Stewart killed me.
Tom Stewart killed me.

527
00:57:33,081 --> 00:57:35,249
Tom Stewart killed me!

528
00:57:35,249 --> 00:57:37,961
Tom Stewart killed me!

529
00:57:37,961 --> 00:57:40,748
Tom Stewart killed me!

530
00:57:51,182 --> 00:57:54,269
So, you and cuckoo-bird have fun
sneaking out last night?

531
00:57:54,269 --> 00:57:56,980
(SIGHS) Go away.

532
00:57:56,980 --> 00:57:58,731
You could have gotten us
all in trouble.

533
00:57:58,731 --> 00:58:00,692
We were looking for Iris.

534
00:58:00,692 --> 00:58:01,687
And?

535
00:58:05,738 --> 00:58:07,282
We couldn't find her.

536
00:58:07,282 --> 00:58:09,993
Well, you probably weren't
looking in the right places.

537
00:58:09,993 --> 00:58:11,487
Not with Magellan over there.

538
00:58:15,790 --> 00:58:17,625
What are you saying?
Nothing.

539
00:58:17,625 --> 00:58:19,711
I saw the two of you
sneaking around last night.

540
00:58:19,711 --> 00:58:22,005
(WHISPERS) Shut up.
They're watching.

541
00:58:22,005 --> 00:58:23,923
Well, can you blame them?

542
00:58:23,923 --> 00:58:26,259
Just because I was brave enough
to go through with it...

543
00:58:26,259 --> 00:58:29,762
Well, maybe next time
you'll do us all a favour and get it right.

544
00:58:29,762 --> 00:58:32,765
(GASPS) Boo-hoo. Timid little Zoey.

545
00:58:32,765 --> 00:58:35,935
Why don't you crawl into your shell
and hide, just like a little turtle?

546
00:58:35,935 --> 00:58:37,895
Why don't you leave her alone?

547
00:58:37,895 --> 00:58:41,608
What's the matter... Daddy didn't
pay enough attention to you?

548
00:58:41,608 --> 00:58:44,569
Mind your own business.
Why don't you leave us all alone?

549
00:58:44,569 --> 00:58:46,561
I mean, nobody likes you.

550
00:58:47,905 --> 00:58:49,449
Well, you're just jealous.

551
00:58:49,449 --> 00:58:50,783
Of what?
Of me.

552
00:58:50,783 --> 00:58:52,160
(LAUGHS)

553
00:58:52,160 --> 00:58:54,078
You've been jealous of me
since I got here.

554
00:58:54,078 --> 00:58:56,706
I am tired of putting up with
your pathetic behaviour, and...

555
00:58:56,706 --> 00:58:58,995
(TURNS TV UP)
I can't hear you!

556
00:59:06,633 --> 00:59:08,791
They're all just jealous of me.

557
00:59:12,096 --> 00:59:14,136
Let's see Roy say no to this.

558
00:59:17,727 --> 00:59:18,925
(SHRIEKS)

559
00:59:34,035 --> 00:59:37,119
(TV DRONES LOUDLY)

560
01:00:01,771 --> 01:00:03,439
(SCREAMS)

561
01:00:03,439 --> 01:00:05,479
(MOANS)

562
01:00:22,542 --> 01:00:24,794
No! Ah, no!

563
01:00:24,794 --> 01:00:26,879
Please let me go.
Please let me out of here!

564
01:00:26,879 --> 01:00:30,341
Alice, it wasn't my idea, I swear!

565
01:00:30,341 --> 01:00:32,302
They made me do... (YELPS)

566
01:00:32,302 --> 01:00:34,762
No, stop! NO!

567
01:00:34,762 --> 01:00:37,932
No, please don't do this! No!

568
01:00:37,932 --> 01:00:40,268
Just let me go! Alice!

569
01:00:40,268 --> 01:00:42,353
No, please don't do this!

570
01:00:42,353 --> 01:00:45,315
No! Please don't do this!

571
01:00:45,315 --> 01:00:48,192
No! NO!

572
01:00:48,192 --> 01:00:51,277
(ELECTRICITY CRACKLES)

573
01:01:16,054 --> 01:01:19,304
(SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY)

574
01:01:37,992 --> 01:01:39,486
Where's Sarah?

575
01:01:52,966 --> 01:01:54,717
Sarah? No!

576
01:01:54,717 --> 01:01:56,678
(SIGHS)

577
01:01:56,678 --> 01:01:58,221
Where's Sarah?

578
01:01:58,221 --> 01:02:00,640
If Alice got Sarah,
she'll get us all.

579
01:02:00,640 --> 01:02:03,977
No! No, no, no, no!

580
01:02:03,977 --> 01:02:06,384
(SOBS)

581
01:02:14,320 --> 01:02:15,814
Alice Hudson.

582
01:02:18,366 --> 01:02:20,034
This was hers?

583
01:02:20,034 --> 01:02:22,662
I didn't touch her!

584
01:02:22,662 --> 01:02:27,454
It was Sarah and... the other girls!

585
01:02:31,629 --> 01:02:33,423
What did you do to her?

586
01:02:33,423 --> 01:02:35,717
I don't know what she's talking about.

587
01:02:35,717 --> 01:02:37,760
Yes, you do.
You shut up, Zoey!

588
01:02:37,760 --> 01:02:39,762
This isn't a game!

589
01:02:39,762 --> 01:02:42,557
What did you do to her?

590
01:02:42,557 --> 01:02:45,095
Why does she want to kill us?

591
01:02:47,312 --> 01:02:48,855
What did they do to her?

592
01:02:48,855 --> 01:02:50,398
Zoey...

593
01:02:50,398 --> 01:02:52,650
Look, please, Zoey...

594
01:02:52,650 --> 01:02:55,402
I need to know.

595
01:02:56,904 --> 01:02:59,609
A-Alice was bad.

596
01:03:01,743 --> 01:03:03,703
She hurt us.

597
01:03:03,703 --> 01:03:06,620
She hurt us all the time.

598
01:03:07,707 --> 01:03:10,335
Tammy told us what to do.

599
01:03:10,335 --> 01:03:12,045
Tammy was here before you.

600
01:03:12,045 --> 01:03:16,042
She said she could make it stop.

601
01:03:17,967 --> 01:03:20,345
It was her idea.

602
01:03:20,345 --> 01:03:24,841
So... we got rid of her.

603
01:03:26,517 --> 01:03:27,560
Alice?

604
01:03:27,560 --> 01:03:28,935
What?

605
01:03:30,939 --> 01:03:33,512
I know where your bunny is.

606
01:03:36,277 --> 01:03:38,780
You found it?
Yeah.

607
01:03:38,780 --> 01:03:41,401
It's in Tammy's room.

608
01:03:46,204 --> 01:03:48,113
That's mine. You can't have it!

609
01:03:51,751 --> 01:03:54,538
(ALICE MOANS MUFFLEDLY)

610
01:04:17,860 --> 01:04:19,696
ZOEY: We all helped.

611
01:04:19,696 --> 01:04:22,740
And now she's going to kill us all.

612
01:04:22,740 --> 01:04:25,159
We had to.

613
01:04:25,159 --> 01:04:27,120
She was horrible.

614
01:04:27,120 --> 01:04:29,831
Then why is she after me?

615
01:04:29,831 --> 01:04:32,250
What's it matter? We're all dead.

616
01:04:32,250 --> 01:04:35,378
Emily... Emily!

617
01:04:35,378 --> 01:04:36,872
Emily!

618
01:04:39,632 --> 01:04:42,510
We have to get out of here. OK?

619
01:04:42,510 --> 01:04:44,512
But what about Emily?

620
01:04:44,512 --> 01:04:46,006
We'll get her.

621
01:04:47,849 --> 01:04:48,891
Alright?

622
01:04:48,891 --> 01:04:49,971
Come on.

623
01:04:55,440 --> 01:04:57,817
Emily, what are you doing?

624
01:04:57,817 --> 01:04:59,893
I'm not strong like you.

625
01:05:02,488 --> 01:05:04,115
Put the knife down.

626
01:05:04,115 --> 01:05:06,701
I can't!

627
01:05:06,701 --> 01:05:09,073
We're gonna get out of here.

628
01:05:14,917 --> 01:05:16,875
(SCREAMS)

629
01:05:22,216 --> 01:05:23,760
Emily!

630
01:05:23,760 --> 01:05:27,093
(ZOEY SOBS)

631
01:05:37,774 --> 01:05:40,609
No, no, no, no! This can't be happening.

632
01:05:42,779 --> 01:05:44,614
Please don't let her get me!

633
01:05:44,614 --> 01:05:46,108
I don't wanna die!

634
01:05:49,452 --> 01:05:50,946
Zoey...

635
01:05:52,121 --> 01:05:53,616
Do you trust me?

636
01:05:59,045 --> 01:06:00,588
Open the door.

637
01:06:00,588 --> 01:06:02,215
Where did you get that?

638
01:06:02,215 --> 01:06:05,343
Open the door now.

639
01:06:05,343 --> 01:06:08,429
Calm down. Don't do
anything you'll regret.

640
01:06:08,429 --> 01:06:10,098
(OVER P.A.)
We have an incident in progress.

641
01:06:10,098 --> 01:06:11,758
Open the goddamn door!

642
01:06:14,227 --> 01:06:17,263
(ZOEY WHIMPERS)

643
01:06:19,274 --> 01:06:21,150
Hey...
Hey, back up!

644
01:06:21,150 --> 01:06:22,193
Easy...
Back up!

645
01:06:22,193 --> 01:06:24,731
Calm down.
Back up.

646
01:06:27,657 --> 01:06:30,034
Go to the wall.

647
01:06:30,034 --> 01:06:32,786
Back up! Against the wall.

648
01:06:39,043 --> 01:06:40,537
Come on.

649
01:06:51,889 --> 01:06:53,558
Back up!

650
01:06:53,558 --> 01:06:56,394
Back up. Back up!
You can't do this.

651
01:06:56,394 --> 01:06:58,896
Watch me!
You're only hurting yourself.

652
01:06:58,896 --> 01:07:01,232
What are you gonna do, Kristen?
Where are you gonna go?

653
01:07:01,232 --> 01:07:03,189
Away from here.
C'mon, drop the knife.

654
01:07:09,032 --> 01:07:12,619
No! No, let me go! You don't get it!

655
01:07:12,619 --> 01:07:15,121
You don't get it!

656
01:07:15,121 --> 01:07:18,374
Alice Hudson is trying to kill us!

657
01:07:18,374 --> 01:07:20,918
Enough.
You can't be serious.

658
01:07:20,918 --> 01:07:23,421
No, please!
Alright, Kristen. Kristen, Kristen...

659
01:07:23,421 --> 01:07:24,964
I need you to calm down.

660
01:07:24,964 --> 01:07:27,342
That girl is a hopeless case
and you know it.

661
01:07:27,342 --> 01:07:29,093
Luckily that's not your call to make.

662
01:07:29,093 --> 01:07:30,970
You honestly think you can cure her?

663
01:07:30,970 --> 01:07:33,181
I have to try.

664
01:07:33,181 --> 01:07:34,974
I need more time with her, that's all.

665
01:07:34,974 --> 01:07:36,893
You're as hopeless as she is.

666
01:07:36,893 --> 01:07:38,728
You could spend 100 years with her...

667
01:07:38,728 --> 01:07:39,896
Ahh!

668
01:07:39,896 --> 01:07:42,766
(SCREAMS) No! No!

669
01:07:45,985 --> 01:07:48,237
Please... please listen to me!

670
01:07:48,237 --> 01:07:50,615
Get her in a straitjacket
and lock her in her room.

671
01:07:50,615 --> 01:07:53,076
Doctor.
You don't understand...

672
01:07:53,076 --> 01:07:57,821
No... we...

673
01:08:04,921 --> 01:08:06,756
I'm sorry.

674
01:08:06,756 --> 01:08:08,749
I'm so sorry.

675
01:08:20,603 --> 01:08:22,897
You need to get some rest.

676
01:08:22,897 --> 01:08:24,816
Come on.

677
01:08:24,816 --> 01:08:27,223
Mmm. Mmm!

678
01:08:28,403 --> 01:08:30,276
Down the hatch.

679
01:08:32,323 --> 01:08:33,908
(GASPS)

680
01:08:33,908 --> 01:08:36,862
There. Now, that wasn't so bad, was it?

681
01:08:38,329 --> 01:08:39,954
Sleep tight, sugar.

682
01:09:40,308 --> 01:09:42,016
(COUGHS)

683
01:10:04,040 --> 01:10:05,036
(GRUNTS)

684
01:10:11,005 --> 01:10:12,120
(LOCKS DOOR)

685
01:10:18,221 --> 01:10:20,348
(GRUNTS)

686
01:10:20,348 --> 01:10:22,554
Sleep tight, sugar.

687
01:10:23,810 --> 01:10:25,645
Where are we going?

688
01:10:25,645 --> 01:10:27,139
We're getting out of here.

689
01:10:48,710 --> 01:10:51,201
(SCREAMS) Open this door now!

690
01:11:10,565 --> 01:11:13,649
(LIFT WHIRRS)

691
01:11:20,825 --> 01:11:21,993
Stop!

692
01:11:21,993 --> 01:11:25,330
Sonofabitch! Don't you close that...!

693
01:11:25,330 --> 01:11:28,082
Don't you close that goddamn...!

694
01:11:28,082 --> 01:11:31,002
(POUNDS ON DOOR)

695
01:11:31,002 --> 01:11:34,501
He's really mad.

696
01:11:40,136 --> 01:11:43,754
(ALARM BELL RINGS)

697
01:11:45,224 --> 01:11:47,051
Hey! Get back here!

698
01:12:10,166 --> 01:12:11,577
Wait!

699
01:12:18,758 --> 01:12:20,301
We're trapped!

700
01:12:20,301 --> 01:12:22,095
Maybe not. Here, come on.

701
01:12:22,095 --> 01:12:23,221
Come on!

702
01:12:23,221 --> 01:12:24,715
Zoey, take this.

703
01:12:29,269 --> 01:12:30,763
Come on.

704
01:12:36,985 --> 01:12:39,195
Maybe this goes to the first floor, right?

705
01:12:39,195 --> 01:12:40,737
I'll go first.
Alright. Come on.

706
01:12:42,073 --> 01:12:45,034
Send it back as fast as you can, alright?
I will.

707
01:12:45,034 --> 01:12:46,528
(BUZZ!)

708
01:13:04,554 --> 01:13:05,597
Hey!

709
01:13:05,597 --> 01:13:07,388
Open this door!

710
01:13:17,233 --> 01:13:18,514
Fuck.

711
01:13:25,742 --> 01:13:27,485
Come on.

712
01:13:38,671 --> 01:13:40,331
(GRUNTS)

713
01:14:00,818 --> 01:14:02,313
Zoey?

714
01:14:04,072 --> 01:14:05,447
Zoey!

715
01:14:11,537 --> 01:14:13,032
Zoey!

716
01:14:51,536 --> 01:14:53,113
(DROPS PHONE)

717
01:15:05,592 --> 01:15:07,218
(ROARS)

718
01:15:07,218 --> 01:15:08,463
(GRUNTS)

719
01:15:13,266 --> 01:15:14,760
(ROARS)

720
01:15:19,439 --> 01:15:21,182
(SCREAMS)

721
01:15:34,787 --> 01:15:36,994
(SCREAMS)

722
01:15:44,297 --> 01:15:46,507
(ROARS)

723
01:15:46,507 --> 01:15:49,045
(WHIMPERS)

724
01:17:02,792 --> 01:17:04,452
What's going on?
What?!

725
01:17:12,260 --> 01:17:15,430
Answers. No lies this time
or I swear to God...

726
01:17:15,430 --> 01:17:17,506
Now!

727
01:17:18,641 --> 01:17:20,183
The truth.

728
01:17:25,398 --> 01:17:27,108
Your name...

729
01:17:27,108 --> 01:17:31,651
...is Alice Lee Hudson.

730
01:17:46,127 --> 01:17:47,158
May I?

731
01:18:05,396 --> 01:18:09,311
You were abducted from your home
the night of September 3, 1958.

732
01:18:15,698 --> 01:18:17,200
I'm Kristen,

733
01:18:17,200 --> 01:18:19,160
not Alice.

734
01:18:19,160 --> 01:18:20,787
I'm Kristen!

735
01:18:20,787 --> 01:18:23,831
You were left chained up in the
basement of an abandoned farmhouse

736
01:18:23,831 --> 01:18:25,541
for nearly two months...

737
01:18:25,541 --> 01:18:29,462
the same farmhouse you burned down.

738
01:18:29,462 --> 01:18:33,216
You were only 11 years old.

739
01:18:33,216 --> 01:18:37,303
Half-starved, sick with fever,
trapped in the darkness,

740
01:18:37,303 --> 01:18:39,430
it was a waking nightmare.

741
01:18:39,430 --> 01:18:43,893
Your only escape was into delusion.

742
01:18:43,893 --> 01:18:48,888
In order to survive the trauma,
your psyche fractured.

743
01:18:51,651 --> 01:18:55,020
You suffer from multiple
personality disorder.

744
01:18:57,991 --> 01:19:03,246
Each personality took
a piece of this nightmare

745
01:19:03,246 --> 01:19:06,081
and locked it away from you
for your own protection.

746
01:19:07,709 --> 01:19:12,380
But the new personalities
became so... dominant

747
01:19:12,380 --> 01:19:15,675
they completely overwhelmed
Alice's personality.

748
01:19:15,675 --> 01:19:18,177
(ELECTRICITY CRACKLES)

749
01:19:18,177 --> 01:19:22,640
I know it hasn't been pleasant.

750
01:19:22,640 --> 01:19:25,602
But my techniques are helping you.

751
01:19:25,602 --> 01:19:27,729
After several years of therapy,

752
01:19:27,729 --> 01:19:30,857
we've been able to isolate
your different identities.

753
01:19:30,857 --> 01:19:34,110
We'd just begun to single them out
and eliminate them

754
01:19:34,110 --> 01:19:36,487
through some experimental techniques

755
01:19:36,487 --> 01:19:38,694
when you, Kristen, appeared.

756
01:19:43,328 --> 01:19:45,830
I didn't just appear!

757
01:19:45,830 --> 01:19:48,166
Your psyche invented Kristen
to protect itself

758
01:19:48,166 --> 01:19:50,668
from having to relive this trauma.

759
01:19:50,668 --> 01:19:53,503
(STEADY CLICKING)

760
01:20:09,479 --> 01:20:12,314
And now it's time to say goodbye.

761
01:20:15,944 --> 01:20:17,604
(ROARS)

762
01:20:22,867 --> 01:20:24,492
Please don't kill me.

763
01:20:37,298 --> 01:20:40,718
(PANTS)

764
01:20:40,718 --> 01:20:43,672
Don't move. It's OK.

765
01:20:47,433 --> 01:20:49,185
(FILM PROJECTOR WHIRRS)

766
01:20:49,185 --> 01:20:51,271
GIRL ON RECORDING:
She's the last one who got out.

767
01:20:51,271 --> 01:20:53,606
What did you say?

768
01:20:53,606 --> 01:20:59,070
STRINGER: Iris, you know we don't
discuss people who aren't present.

769
01:20:59,070 --> 01:21:01,197
GIRL: She can't remember the rules

770
01:21:01,197 --> 01:21:04,742
because she's the crazy one
around here, you know?

771
01:21:04,742 --> 01:21:06,984
MAN: That's enough.

772
01:21:14,002 --> 01:21:15,496
Is she cured?

773
01:21:17,046 --> 01:21:19,507
She'll probably need
a lifetime of therapy,

774
01:21:19,507 --> 01:21:22,302
but she's no longer a danger to herself.

775
01:21:22,302 --> 01:21:28,138
She is, essentially...
your daughter again.

776
01:21:29,225 --> 01:21:30,719
Can we please see her now?

777
01:21:34,897 --> 01:21:36,226
Alice?

778
01:21:43,197 --> 01:21:45,071
Honey, are you OK?

779
01:21:47,410 --> 01:21:49,662
We love you, sweetheart.

780
01:21:49,662 --> 01:21:52,284
Mom?

781
01:21:53,374 --> 01:21:54,417
Dad?

782
01:21:54,417 --> 01:21:56,457
Oh, honey...

783
01:22:06,304 --> 01:22:10,349
I figured you'd... want
your things around you.

784
01:22:16,689 --> 01:22:19,311
And I put this one
back together for you too.

785
01:22:22,904 --> 01:22:24,528
Thank you.

786
01:22:40,046 --> 01:22:43,883
I think I remember...
What do you remember?

787
01:22:43,883 --> 01:22:46,718
Everything.

788
01:22:48,638 --> 01:22:50,390
The old farmhouse.

789
01:22:50,390 --> 01:22:52,934
This place.

790
01:22:52,934 --> 01:22:54,769
The others.

791
